S'  This short note provides a minor correction to the sufficient conditions, and\nalso a small extension of the structural results for Partially Observed Markov\nDecision Processes (POMDPs) given in [Lovejoy 1987] and [Rieder 1991].\nSufficient conditions are provided so that the optimal policy can be upper and\nlower bounded by judiciously chosen myopic policies. These myopic policy bounds\nare constructed to maximize the volume of belief states where they coincide\nwith the optimal policy. Numerical examples illustrate these myopic bounds for\nboth continuous and discrete observation sets.\n'
