S'  In this article, we consider mean field games between a dominating player and\na group of representative agents, each of which acts similarly and also\ninteracts with each other through a mean field term being substantially\ninfluenced by the dominating player. We first provide the general theory and\ndiscuss the necessary condition for the optimal controls and game condition by\nadopting adjoint equation approach. We then present a special case in the\ncontext of linear-quadratic framework, in which a necessary and sufficient\ncondition can be asserted by stochastic maximum principle; we finally establish\nthe sufficient condition that guarantees the unique existence of the\nequilibrium control. The proof of the convergence result of finite player game\nto mean field counterpart is provided in Appendix.\n'
