S'  In this paper, we consider the approximate controllability of partial\ndifferential equations with time derivatives of non-integer order via boundary\ncontrol. We first show the unique existence of the solution under smooth\nboundary conditions using the eigenfunction expansion. Next we also study the\ndual system and apply their results to prove (i) the regularity of the solution\nwith non-smooth boundary conditions and (ii) approximate controllability.\n'
